Edit platform/cli/src/commands/audit.ts lines 122-128. The issue is on line 125:
```
const status = (entry.success ? pc.green('\u2713') : pc.red('\u2717')).padEnd(statusCol);
```

padEnd counts ANSI escape codes as characters, so the visual padding is wrong. Fix by padding the raw string first, then colorizing:
```
const statusChar = entry.success ? '\u2713' : '\u2717';
const statusPadded = statusChar.padEnd(statusCol);
const status = entry.success ? pc.green(statusPadded) : pc.red(statusPadded);
```

Or: apply color to the character only, then manually add spaces:
```
const statusIcon = entry.success ? pc.green('\u2713') : pc.red('\u2717');
const status = statusIcon + ' '.repeat(Math.max(0, statusCol - 1));
```

The second approach is more robust since checkmark/cross are single visual characters.
